quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  11,1,"Alif. Lam. Ra. This is a Divine Command whose contents have been made firm and set forth in detail from One Who is All-Wise, All-Aware"{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  11,2,"that you may worship none but Allah. Verily, I have come to you as a warner and a bearer of good news from Him"
  11,3,"that you may seek forgiveness of your Lord and turn to Him in repentance whereupon He will grant you a fair enjoyment of life until an appointed term, and will bestow favour on everyone who merits favour. But should you turn away (from the truth), I fear for you the chastisement of an Awesome Day."{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  11,4,"Unto Allah is your return, and He has power to do everything."
  11,5,"Lo! They fold up their breasts that they may conceal themselves from Him. Surely when they cover themselves up with their garments Allah knows well what they cover and what they reveal. Indeed He even knows the secrets hidden in the breasts."{1},footnotes:1:1